Shopping Cart

-- LLD requirements

Functional Requirements:

1. User should be able to add/update/remove items to the cart.
2. System should be able to calculate price once the products are added/updated
3. System should be able to reflect changes in the prices.
4. System should be able to sync data across devices.
5. System should be able to store details in the cart.
6. System should be able to display once the product goes out of stock.

Non Functional Requirements:

1. Availability
2. Low Latency
3. Scalable
4. Eventual Consistency
5. Durability

Entities

1. Cart
2. Product
3. User
4. CartItem


Edge Cases:

1.Multiple users adding product at the same time -- check quantity at checkout
2.Price updated during checkout -- refresh at checkout
3.User accessing from multiple devices -- optimistic locking
4.Multiple users removing product from cart -- check quantity at checkout
5.Product goes out of stock after adding to cart --  check quantity at checkout/update isAvailable to false
6.Cart expiry / abandoned cart -- use last updated and expire after certain time
7.Price mismatch during payment -- Final validation BEFORE payment

